value.name: About Form 2848, Power of Attorney and Declaration of Representative
value.snippet: Use Form 2848 to authorize an individual to represent you before the IRS. The individual you authorize must be a person eligible to practice before the IRS. You may authorize a student who works in a qualified Low Income Taxpayer Clinic (LITC) or Student Tax Clinic Program (STCP) to represent you under a special appearance authorization issued by the Taxpayer Advocate Service.

value.name: IRS Power of Attorney Form 2848 | Revised Jan. 2021
value.snippet: An IRS power of attorney form 2848 is a document used when designating someone else (accountant) to file federal taxes on behalf of an entity or individual. The acts authorized here allow a tax attorney or accountant to represent someone else and to submit taxes to the Internal Revenue Service on the principal’s behalf.

value.name: Irs Form 2848 ≡ Fill Out Printable PDF Forms Online
value.snippet: Irs Form 2848 is a document designed by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) to enable taxpayers to appoint an individual or organization to represent them in tax matters. The form, which can be completed either electronically or in paper form, allows the representative to handle routine tasks and communicate with the IRS on behalf of the taxpayer.
